  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1385457126" />
    <a title="Susanne Matthews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23177247-susanne-matthews"><img alt="Susanne Matthews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491145985p2/23177247.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1385457126?book_show_action=true">Sep 07, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Susanne Matthews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Susanne Matthews" href="/user/show/23177247-susanne-matthews">Susanne Matthews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/26235680-a-french-kiss-in-london">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1385457126" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8190961153175461993">Ms. De Ross&apos;s second novel, is a beautiful love story between an Italian sculptress and a French cancer researcher who seeks his potential cures and treatments in old world science and nature. The book demonstrates Ms. De Ross&apos;s growth as an author and her increased facility with the English language. The story is easy to follow and provides snippets of information about her homeland, Romania, which I found fascinating. While I would have liked to have seen the paranormal elements of the story d</span>
  <span id="freeText8190961153175461993" style="display:none">Ms. De Ross's second novel, is a beautiful love story between an Italian sculptress and a French cancer researcher who seeks his potential cures and treatments in old world science and nature. The book demonstrates Ms. De Ross's growth as an author and her increased facility with the English language. The story is easy to follow and provides snippets of information about her homeland, Romania, which I found fascinating. While I would have liked to have seen the paranormal elements of the story developed further, I enjoyed the story and its happily ever after ending.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8190961153175461993" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


